name: Bulbasaur
flavorText: There is a plant seed on its back right from the day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly grows larger.

name: Ivysaur
flavorText: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Venusaur
flavorText: Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may flip a coin. If heads, switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon, and the new Active Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

name: Radiant Venusaur
flavorText: Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.
Ability1Text: Once at the end of your turn (after your attack), you may use this Ability. Draw cards until you have 4 cards in your hand.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned, Confused, and Poisoned.

name: Alolan Exeggutor V
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for up to 5 Grass Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon for each Grass Energy attached to this Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Spinarak
flavorText: Although the poison from its fangs isn't that strong, it's potent enough to weaken prey that gets caught in its web.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Ariados
flavorText: It spews threads from its mouth to catch its prey. When night falls, it leaves its web to go hunt aggressively.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.
Attack2Text: Heal 50 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Charmander
flavorText: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.
Attack2Text: Discard a Fire Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Charizard
flavorText: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.
Ability1Text: Each basic Fire Energy attached to your Pokémon provides FireFire Energy. You can't apply more than 1 Burn Brightly Ability at a time.
Attack1Text: Discard all Fire Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Radiant Charizard
flavorText: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon's attacks cost Colorless less for each Prize card your opponent has taken.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Combustion Blast.

name: Moltres
flavorText: It's one of the legendary bird Pokémon. When Moltres flaps its flaming wings, they glimmer with a dazzling red glow.
Ability1Text: Your Basic Fire Pokémon's attacks, except any Moltres, do 10 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Numel
flavorText: The magma in its body reaches 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit. Its hump gets smaller when it uses Fire-type moves.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Camerupt
flavorText: If angered, the humps on its back erupt in a shower of molten lava. It lives in the craters of volcanoes.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Squirtle
flavorText: When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force.

name: Wartortle
flavorText: It is recognized as a symbol of longevity. If its shell has algae on it, that Wartortle is very old.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Blastoise
flavorText: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 6 Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Radiant Blastoise
flavorText: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.
Ability1Text: You must discard a Water Energy card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Torrential Cannon.

name: Slowpoke
flavorText: Slow-witted and oblivious, this Pokémon won't feel any pain if its tail gets eaten. It won't notice when its tail grows back, either.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Put an Item card from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Slowbro
flavorText: Slowpoke became Slowbro when a Shellder bit on to its tail. Sweet flavors seeping from the tail make the Shellder feel as if its life is a dream.
Attack1Text: Both Active Pokémon are now Asleep.
Attack2Text: You can use this attack only if your opponent has exactly 1 Prize card remaining. Take 2 Prize cards.

name: Magikarp
flavorText: It is virtually worthless in terms of both power and speed. It is the most weak and pathetic Pokémon in the world.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for any number of Magikarp, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Magikarp and Gyarados in your discard pile.

name: Gyarados
flavorText: It has an extremely aggressive nature. The Hyper Beam it shoots from its mouth totally incinerates all targets.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, discard the top 2 cards of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: Discard the top 5 cards of your deck.

name: Lapras
flavorText: A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Articuno
flavorText: It's said that this Pokémon's beautiful blue wings are made of ice. Articuno flies over snowy mountains, its long tail fluttering along behind it.
Ability1Text: Your Basic Water Pokémon's attacks, except any Articuno, do 10 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Wimpod
flavorText: It's nature's cleaner—it eats anything and everything, including garbage and rotten things. The ground near its nest is always clean.
Ability1Text: If your opponent has any Pokémon V in play, this Pokémon has no Retreat Cost.

name: Golisopod
flavorText: It will do anything to win, taking advantage of every opening and finishing opponents off with the small claws on its front legs.
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon moved from your Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.
Attack1Text: If you played a Supporter card from your hand during this turn, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Zapdos
flavorText: This Pokémon has complete control over electricity. There are tales of Zapdos nesting in the dark depths of pitch-black thunderclouds.
Ability1Text: Your Basic Lightning Pokémon's attacks, except any Zapdos, do 10 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Mewtwo V
Attack2Text: Move an Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Mewtwo VSTAR
Attack1Text: Discard up to 3 Psychic Energy from your Pokémon. This attack does 90 damage for each card you discarded in this way.
Attack2Text: This attack does 120 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon V. This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Natu
flavorText: It is extremely good at climbing tree trunks and likes to eat the new sprouts on the trees.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Xatu
flavorText: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.
Attack1Text: This attack does 90 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon V. This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Lunatone
flavorText: The phase of the moon apparently has some effect on its power. It's active on the night of a full moon.
Attack1Text: Discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Sylveon
flavorText: By releasing enmity-erasing waves from its ribbonlike feelers, Sylveon stops any conflict.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Dragon Pokémon, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Onix
flavorText: As it digs through the ground, it absorbs many hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

name: Larvitar
flavorText: Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Pupitar
flavorText: Even sealed in its shell, it can move freely. Hard and fast, it has outstanding destructive power.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Solrock
flavorText: When it rotates itself, it gives off light similar to the sun, thus blinding its foes.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Psychic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Lunatone.

name: Conkeldurr V
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does that much more damage.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 90 more damage, and your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Alolan Rattata
flavorText: Night after night, they sneak into people's homes seeking food. A massive outbreak of them has become an issue of public concern.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Alolan Raticate
flavorText: It commands a nest of Rattata. Different nests don't get along, whipping up severe fights over feeding grounds.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Put damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon until its remaining HP is 10.

name: Tyranitar
flavorText: Its body can't be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage for each damage counter on all of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Steelix
flavorText: It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Meltan
flavorText: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Melmetal
flavorText: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 90 more damage for each heads.

name: Melmetal V
Attack1Text: You may attach a Metal Energy card from your hand to this Pokémon.

name: Melmetal VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 more damage for each extra Metal Energy attached to this Pokémon (in addition to this attack's cost). You can't add more than 120 damage in this way.

name: Dragonite V
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Dragonite VSTAR
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.
Attack2Text: Look at the top 12 cards of your deck and attach any number of Water or Lightning Energy cards you find there to your Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Chansey
flavorText: The egg Chansey carries is not only delicious but also packed with nutrition. It's used as a high-class cooking ingredient.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Blissey
flavorText: Whenever a Blissey finds a weakened Pokémon, it will share its egg and offer its care until the other Pokémon is all better.
Attack1Text: Heal all damage from 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Ditto
flavorText: It can reconstitute its entire cellular structure to change into what it sees, but it returns to normal when it relaxes.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon can use the attacks of any Basic Pokémon in your discard pile, except for Pokémon with a Rule Box (Pokémon V, Pokémon-GX, etc. have Rule Boxes). (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)

name: Eevee
evolvesTo: Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Sylveon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon
flavorText: It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.
Attack1Text: Choose a random card from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals that card and shuffles it into their deck.

name: Snorlax
flavorText: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent's Active Pokémon can't retreat.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Aipom
flavorText: It searches for prey from the tops of trees. When it spots its favorite food, Bounsweet, Aipom gets excited and pounces.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Ambipom
flavorText: It uses its tails for everything. If it wraps both of its tails around you and gives you a squeeze, that's proof it really likes you.
Ability1Text: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin for each Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack does 60 damage for each heads.

name: Slaking V
Ability1Text: If you have exactly 2, 4, or 6 Prize cards remaining, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Bidoof
flavorText: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Bibarel
flavorText: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, cards in your deck can't be discarded by effects of your opponent's attacks, Abilities, Item cards, or Supporter cards.

name: Pidove
flavorText: Where people go, these Pokémon follow. If you're scattering food for them, be careful— several hundred of them can gather at once.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon's attacks do 20 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Tranquill
flavorText: It can fly moderately quickly. No matter how far it travels, it can always find its way back to its master and its nest.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Unfezant
flavorText: Unfezant are exceptional fliers. The females are known for their stamina, while the males outclass them in terms of speed.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 70 damage for each heads.

name: Alolan Exeggutor V
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for up to 5 Grass Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon for each Grass Energy attached to this Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Mewtwo V
Attack2Text: Move an Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

Attack1Text: If this Pokémon was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does that much more damage.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 90 more damage, and your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

Attack1Text: If this Pokémon was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does that much more damage.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 90 more damage, and your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Melmetal V
Attack1Text: You may attach a Metal Energy card from your hand to this Pokémon.

name: Dragonite V
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Slaking V
Ability1Text: If you have exactly 2, 4, or 6 Prize cards remaining, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Professor's Research
flavorText: Professor Willow

Attack1Text: Discard up to 3 Psychic Energy from your Pokémon. This attack does 90 damage for each card you discarded in this way.
Attack2Text: This attack does 120 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon V. This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
